<DocsPage
  title="Getting started"
  description="Install Nodus, add your first package, and validate the resulting runtime files."
>
  <p>Install Nodus:</p>
  <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://nodus.elata.ai/install.sh | bash</code></pre>

  <p>Add your first package:</p>
  <pre><code>nodus add nodus-rs/nodus --adapter codex</code></pre>

  <p>That command:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>creates <code>nodus.toml</code> if needed</li>
    <li>records the dependency you asked for</li>
    <li>resolves and locks the exact revision</li>
    <li>writes the adapter runtime files for the enabled tool</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Validate the result:</p>
  <pre><code>nodus doctor</code></pre>

  <p>Common next steps:</p>
  <pre><code>{`nodus info nodus-rs/nodus\nnodus update\nnodus sync --locked`}</code></pre>
</DocsPage>
